---
import { publicUrl } from "../utils/publicUrl";
/**
 * Decorative fake-editor strip before the projects section.
 */
---

<section class="relative border-b border-border/80 bg-surface-muted/25">
	<div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-4 py-10 md:py-12">
		<p class="text-center text-sm font-medium text-muted">
			This isn’t real code—it’s only here to set the mood before the project stories below.
		</p>
		<div class="mt-4 overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-border bg-[#1e1e1e] shadow-md shadow-stone-300/35">
			<img
				src={publicUrl("/code-editor-teaser.svg")}
				width="960"
				height="280"
				class="h-auto w-full object-contain object-top"
				loading="lazy"
				decoding="async"
				alt=""
				role="presentation"
			/>
		</div>
		<p class="mt-3 text-center text-xs text-muted/90">
			The picture is decoration. For each project, read the summary; if there’s a public GitHub link, use the screenshot or the “View on GitHub” button.
		</p>
	</div>
</section>
